Razgulay Plans to Process 1.6 Million Tons of Beets Into Sugar

-- B y   M a r i n a   S y s o y e v a
-- 
2011-08-31T12:45:03Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-31/razgulay-plans-to-process-1-6-million-tons-of-beets-into-sugar.html
OAO Razgulay Group, a Russian sugar,
grain and flour producer, started refining its own sugar beets
and expects to process 1.6 million metric tons this year, the
company said today in an e-mailed statement.  Razgulay sowed 47,000 hectares (116,137 acres) of beets
this year, it said. The company controls 460,000 hectares of
fields, of which 338,000 hectares are in use this year,
according to the statement  To contact the reporter on this story:
Marina Sysoyeva in Moscow at 
 msysoyeva@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
John Viljoen at 
 jviljoen@bloomberg.net  